		      <h3>What is Ghoti?</h3>
			  <p>Ghoti is a tool that keeps track of application boilerplates built around Groovy-based technologies like <a href="http://www.grails.org">Grails</a> and <a href="http://www.gradle.org">Gradle</a>.</p>
			  <p>Starting a new project in Grails? Use Ghoti to download a sample repo from Github already configured with Geb, Webdriver and Spock. Life has just gotten simpler.</p>
			  <p>If you have created a boilerplate, Ghoti helps you share this with other developers like you. </p>
			  <p>Ghoti is heavily inspired by <a href="http://brunch.io/#skeletons-list">Brunch Skeletons</a> and <a href="http://www.gvmtool.net">GVM</a>.. </p>
			  <h3>Usage</h3>
			  <p>To install a template for Ratpack, just call:</p>
			   <pre>  ghoti new ratpack myRatpackApp</pre>
			  <p>This downloads the ratpack sample application so you can start playing with it. Easy as pie.</p> 	
